data.value: The world-famous symbol of Paris As one of the copy structures of the Eiffel Tower, the tower built in Tokyo's Shiba Park is the country's tallest construction of 333 meters. The Tokyo Tower, designed by the famous Japanese architect Tachu Naito, cost an astronomical figure of $ 8.4 billion in 1958. The tower, which has become one of the symbolic structures of the capital, is one of Japan's tourist destinations.
